2001-01-01|2001-12-30.description:
Overview

Continuing the new look at Daredevil's early days by the award-winning team of Jeph Loeb and Tim Sale! Life is pretty good for New York's newest super hero. That is, until he crosses paths with his first super-villain: Electro! Then, the final fate of Jack Murdock's killers changes Matt's life forever! All this... and Karen Page gets kidnapped? Who knew the early days of the Man Without Fear were anything like this?
2001-01-01|2001-12-30.name: Never Lead With Your Left

2001-01-01|2001-12-30.description: King Zapp! Emperor Brannigan! Call him what you will when Zapp travels to the planet Da Nang 4 on a secret mission in the war between DOOP and Da Nang 4 he is made ruler by the inhabitants. His one request? A queen to rule by his side - the sexilicious Leela! The Da Nang 4 people take care of Zapp's every wish and feed him to bloated proportions. In a trip to the Lovenasium Zapp cannot even bring himself to consummate their union. Fry and Bender cook up a plan to steal DOOP's beer supply to recharge Bender's cells and stumble upon the evil plan of Da Nang 4's people as does Leela as she saves the day!
2001-01-01|2001-12-30.name: D.O.O.P. The Right Thing

2001-01-01|2001-12-30.description:
Overview
This four-issue miniseries now in state-of-the-art full-color, reaches its grand finale, as Kei and Yuri struggle with the villainous Kevin Sleet through a nightmarish cyberspace battleground, with the very fate of civilization hanging in the balance! Thrill to gun fetishism, savage beatings, rogue nanotechnology, and even a brief visit to Hell itself! Wheee!!!

2001-01-01|2001-12-30.description: The fourth issue of the best-selling fantasy series of the last descendant of the People of the Stars, Thorgal, living among the medieval Vikings. Black Galley is the beginning of the three-issue subseries, which tells of the fight with the ruler of the island Brek Zarith - Shardara Mighty. Thorgal lives peacefully with his pregnant wife in a safe location - the village lost somewhere on the shores of the North Sea. He put down his sword, helps villagers with the harvest, enjoying an ordinary life away from wars and intrigues. But the gods prefer him as a hero fighting evil, and therefore this idyll can not last long.
